@Comment:	Per grammar.js, `group_with_annotations` REQUIRES at least one
@Comment:	annotation following the `<...>`. When the annotation is absent
@Comment:	(malformed CHAT input), tree-sitter recovers by inserting a
@Comment:	synthetic MISSING `retrace_complete` (visible in
@Comment:	`tree-sitter parse` output as `(MISSING retrace_complete [r,c]-[r,c])`).
@Comment:	The model AST therefore promotes the group to
@Comment:	`Retrace { kind: Full, is_group: true, ... }` whether the [//]
@Comment:	marker is real or synthesized — the two are model-indistinguishable.
@Comment:	Re2c must mirror the recovery so SemanticEq holds; the diagnostic
@Comment:	emission for this recovery path is tracked separately in the
@Comment:	parity-report § MISSING-Token Recovery Policy. Fixture seeded by
@Comment:	tele19a.cha:157 wild-corpus example, 2026-04-30.
*PAR:	<I don't> &-uh I know xxx .
@End
